      "lineNbr": 16,
      "author": {
        "id": 1178685
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-12T05:07:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When you install the deps, npm will look at package-lock.json and install the dependencies of specified version. So as long as you have the same package-lock.json file, you will have exactly the same dependencies installed.\npackage.json specify dependency versions that \"should\" work. When dependencies need to be updated (e.g. add a new dependencies with transitive dependencies), they are still subject to version range specified in package.json, but package-lock.json may be updated accordingly to avoid duplicate dependencies (same library different version) as much as possible.\nIf the package is a library, the dependents don\u0027t need to respect package-lock.json. But they do need to respect package.json.",
      "parentUuid": "60ecda35_9ea351d8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 9,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "b097039f958491e89bb43c0c6a523e3194800c15",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
